Φ(Dispositif) = σ(normal|deviant) ∘ ρ(power|knowledge) ∘ λ(repression|production) ∘ β(surveillance|self_governance) ∘ δγ(emergence|obsolescence) ∘ μ(institution|discourse) + ε | :productive_power

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: normal|deviant — Categories produced by the dispositif itself, defining acceptability within power/knowledge networks.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: power|knowledge — Inseparable nexus where knowledge serves and produces power simultaneously.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: repression|production — Power is not merely repressive but productive, creating subjects, knowledge, and realities.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: surveillance|self_governance — External monitoring grows into internalized self-regulation through norm absorption.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: emergence|obsolescence — Dispositifs arise in response to urgent needs and evolve with shifting dynamics.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: institution|discourse — The heterogeneous ensemble of institutions, laws, and practices composing the network.

## Z-State
:productive_power — Power that creates subjects, knowledge, and social realities rather than merely constraining them.

## Tendency
μ → 0.85

